## 2026-03-28 - Missing ASSET token type validation in core validator.ts
- Added `case TOKEN_TYPES.ASSET` to the validator switch statement, requiring the value to be a string (URI or data-URI). Previously, asset tokens fell through to the `default` case and were silently accepted regardless of value shape.
- Added tests for valid asset values (URLs, data URIs, relative paths) and invalid values (number, boolean, object).
- Files changed: `packages/core/src/validator.ts` ~L200 (new case), `packages/core/src/__tests__/validator.test.ts` ~L404 (new test block)

